  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Engineer",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate, create and edit BIM models.</li>\n  <li>Prepare proposal, shop and as-built drawing.</li>\n  <li>Conduct clash detection and conflict solution.</li>\n  <li>Perform site survey and inspection to ensure precision of drawing.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with contractors to update on any changes and new requirements.</li>\n  <li>Propose model design drawings for contractors and vendor.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and print out as-built drawings for OMM with accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Follow-up as-built drawing based on feedback from clients and consultants.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma with at least 3 years of experience in BIM modelling using AutoCad, preferably in data centre or critical environment.</li>\n  <li><strong>MEP BIM</strong></li>\n  <li>Experienced in modelling and drafting M&amp;E and Fire Protection Services</li>\n  <li>Able to understand other trades that involve electrical and draw electrical drawings in layout and single line diagram.</li>\n  <li><strong>Architectural/Structural</strong></li>\n  <li>Experienced in modelling and drafting Architecture &amp; Civil Structural</li>\n  <li>Able to understand and draw architectural and structural models / drawings.</li>\n  <li>Certification in workplace safety (eg. WSQ, WSH) preferred.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication and collaborative skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
